body.description: Parenting is filled with so many important decisions it can make your head spin. With the jive convertible car seat, you have one less decision to make because you get two seats in one. It keeps your child safe, from 5-65 pounds. Your baby can ride comfortably rear facing up to 40 pounds. When the time comes, your "big kid" can ride forward facing up to 65 pounds. The jive 2-in-1 car seat is perfect for your growing family, too. You can fit 3 (incredibly well-behaved youngsters) in the back seat of most cars. The jive convertible car seat also puts your safety concerns at ease with the built-in side impact protection and 5-point harness. The harness features 5 heights and 3 buckle locations to perfectly fit your growing child. It’s comfortable for kids and convenient for parents, too. The removable insert pillows provide extra head and body support. As your little one grows, The cushions easily remove, and your big kid will love the extra comfy ride that the plush padding provides. Who has time to constantly clean up messes? Certainly not you. The fabric is both machine washable and dryer safe, making this seat super easy to clean when messes happen. Stressed about traveling with kids? The jive convertible car seat is certified for use on an aircraft. Its compact design also makes it easier to manage through airport security checks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My son loves it and I do to!
reviews.reviewText: I am very happy with this carseat that we purchased about 6 months ago. I like that is not extra bulky so it doesn't take up extra space and 2 other passengers can sit in the back of the car next to the carseat, while the carseat is still wide enough that my 2 1/2 year old son can sit comfortably. It was a great price compared to anything else I saw, the look is nice, it was easy for my husband to install and it is easy to strap in my son. The only negative parts are: 1. that the cupholders are always falling out so we usually don't use them. 2. As the child grows you need to adjust the size of the staps and that is not as easy on this carseat as it was in our infant carseat.Overall would definately reccommend this carseat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not good for rear facing!!!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to use in my car for my 20 month old granddaughter that I keep every Friday. It was not any harder to install than any other car seat I have dealt with but it would not tighten enough to keep it from rocking no matter what I did. I tried the rolled up towel trick but that did not work either. My son even tried to tighten it. He ended up using the tether strap on the back of the carseat and hooking it to the front of the actual seat to keep it secured. This is in addition to using the hooks and the lap belt. I am sure it will be fine once we turn her forward facing. But I am disappointed in the fact that they advertised this one for both rear and forward facing.But the worst part aside from not fitting tight enough is the button on the 5 point harness is the most difficult button I have ever had to deal with! It takes me 3 or 4 tries and having to use all the force I have to get this button to release. I am concerned that this is a safety issue.The seat has a nice padded cushion and it looks comfortable. I also like the 2 cup holders. That is great for snacks on the road. It seems easy to clean also. I am so disappointed that it has been so difficult to install and the release button is such a pain.

reviews.reviewText: I bought this for a travel car seat to use with my one year old on the plane and at our destinations. It’s easy to bring with at the airport since it only weighs 10 pounds. It’s easy to install, especially if you lift the fabric up to pull the strap tight.It also fits on my travel stroller perfectly with a strap through the forward facing belt path. (I have the ergo baby metro plus city stroller for reference. It fits in the overhead bin on the plane.)
